ce:section.ce:para:
For AHP adsorbed systems (Fig. 6
                        ) the HOMO-LUMO distributions are: In CC-AHP and BNO-AHP, HOMO is over the AHP while LUMO is over the graphene. In BBP-AHP, HOMO and LUMO are over the entire system, with overlapping orbitals of AHP and BBP in HOMO electron density. In NNP-AHP, both HOMO and LUMO are over the Coronene, while in BNP-AHP, HOMO is over AHP and LUMO is over the Coronene. All these electron density distributions in AHP adsorbed systems, show the charge transfer and chemisorption nature of AHP adsorption. Figure 5 and 7
                        .
